The paper deals with algorithms and complexity related to routing and communication on graphs, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). However, the specific focus on matchings and sorting networks suggests that the paper is more closely related to topics in Graph Theory (cs.GT) and Combinatorics (cs.DM). The use of permutations and NP-Completeness also suggests a connection to Theoretical Computer Science (cs.IT). Finally, the mention of deterministic algorithms and time complexity suggests a connection to Computer Science and Game Theory (cs.CG). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CG, and cs.DM.
